President Obama announced his intent to nominate Jill E. Sommers for another term as a Commissioner of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission (CFTC). Sommers has been serving as a Commissioner since August 2007, and her current term is set to expire in April 2009. She has also served as the Chairman and Designated Federal Official of the Global Markets Advisory Committee and as the Commission designee to the Financial Literacy and Education Commission. Sommers has a background in the commodity futures and options industry, having worked for the International Swaps and Derivatives Association and the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. She started her career in Washington as an intern for Senator Robert J. Dole and later worked for consulting firms specializing in agricultural issues. Sommers holds a Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of Kansas.